  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get affordable shopping experience for floor tiles?",
  "response": "Finding affordable floor tiles can be achieved through various outlets, both online and offline. Here are some suggestions to help you get the best deals:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Local Tile Outlets and Showrooms**\n- **Clearance Sections**: Visit local tile showrooms and check their clearance or discounted sections for overstocked or discontinued items.\n- **Wholesale Dealers**: Look for wholesale tile suppliers in your area. They often offer lower prices when buying in bulk.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Big-Box Retail Stores**\n- **Home Improvement Stores**: Stores like Home Depot, Lowe\u2019s, or Menards often have affordable options and sales.\n- **Warehouse Clubs**: Check out stores like Costco or Sam's Club for discounted tile deals.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Online Retailers**\n- **Amazon**: Offers a wide range of tiles at competitive prices, especially during sales events.\n- **Wayfair**: Known for home goods, Wayfair often has discounted tiles.\n- **Overstock**: Specializes in discounted home improvement products, including tiles.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Discount Tile Stores**\n- **Floor & Decor**: A popular chain with a wide selection of affordable tiles.\n- **Habitat for Humanity ReStores**: These nonprofit stores sell donated tiles and other building materials at low prices.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Online Marketplaces**\n- **eBay**: Look for new and unused tiles sold by individuals or businesses.\n- **Facebook Marketplace**: A great way to find local deals on tiles or leftover materials from other projects.\n- **Craigslist**: Check for local sellers offering tiles at discounted prices.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Direct from Manufacturers**\n- Some tile manufacturers sell directly to consumers at lower prices. Look for local or online manufacturers in your area.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Garage Sales or Estate Sales**\n- Occasionally, you can find leftover tiles from renovations at garage or estate sales.\n\n---\n\n### **Money-Saving Tips**\n- **Buy in Bulk**: Many retailers offer discounts for larger quantities.\n- **Look for Sales and Promotions**: Many stores have seasonal sales or holiday discounts.\n- **Consider Porcelain or Ceramic**: These materials are often more affordable than natural stone or luxury tiles.\n- **Check for Free Samples**: Some stores offer free tile samples to help you decide without committing to a purchase.\n\nBy exploring these options, you can find high-quality tiles at affordable prices for your flooring project.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
